leads.lead_text: Tree to 40 m tall; leaves of mature crown broadly lanceolate to lanceolate, 9–14 cm long; forest trees of East Gippsland
Small, spreading trees; leaves of mature crown orbicular to ovate, rarely lanceolate, 4–8 cm long
Adult leaves green or blue-green; buds non-waxy; small trees or mallees of North-and West-central Victoria, the eastern Wimmera and the Brisbane Ranges
Adult leaves glaucous; buds waxy; spreading trees of eastern and central Victoria
